Title: The M(atrix) model/adS_2 correspondence
Authors: P.K. Townsend
Comments: 9 pp. Latex. Revised to include corrections, improvements and
  additional references. To appear in Proceedings of the 3'rd Puri workshop on
  Quantum Field Theory, Quantum Gravity and Strings, Puri, Orissa, India,
  December 9-19, 1998
Report-no: DAMTP-1999-33
\\
  The M(atrix) model has a dual realization as IIA superstring theory in the
near-horizon geometry of the supergravity D0-brane. The role of $adS_2$ in this
correspondence is reviewed, and some aspects of holography that it suggests are
discussed.
